@startuml
title Final Project - Finance Diagram

left to right direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam nodesep 70
skinparam ranksep 70
hide methods
hide circle

skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ArrowColor #475569
skinparam PackageBorderColor #334155
skinparam PackageBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam ClassBorderColor #334155
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor white

package "4) Finance" {
    class User {
        +id
        +name
        +requested_role
        +approved_at
    }

    class Course {
        +id
        +code
        +name
        +price
    }

    class StudentTuition {
        +id
        +course_price
    }

    class TuitionPayment {
        +id
        +amount
        +paid_on
        +method
    }

    class EmployeePayment {
        +id
        +expected_salary
        +amount_paid
    }

    class ScholarshipActivation {
        +id
        +offer_key
        +discount_percent
        +activated_at
    }
}

User "1" <-- "0..1" StudentTuition : tuition profile for student
Course "1" <-- "0..*" StudentTuition : selected course
StudentTuition "1" .. "0..*" TuitionPayment : settled by payments

User "1" <-- "0..*" TuitionPayment : payment for student
User "0..1" <-- "0..*" TuitionPayment : paid by parent
User "0..1" <-- "0..*" TuitionPayment : recorded by staff

User "1" <-- "0..1" EmployeePayment : salary record for employee
User "0..1" <-- "0..*" EmployeePayment : recorded by staff

User "1" <-- "0..*" ScholarshipActivation : activated by parent
User "0..1" <-- "0..*" ScholarshipActivation : applied to student

User -[hidden]-> Course
Course -[hidden]-> StudentTuition
StudentTuition -[hidden]-> TuitionPayment
TuitionPayment -[hidden]-> EmployeePayment
EmployeePayment -[hidden]-> ScholarshipActivation

note bottom of TuitionPayment
Payments are stored against users in the codebase.
The dotted link to StudentTuition represents the
business flow used by the financial services.
end note

@enduml
